1. Install JDK 8
2. Install Anaconda in the Cloudera VM
Go to the link below and download Python 3.7 Version
https://www.anaconda.com/distribution/#download-section

Open Terminal and change the permission for the downloaded script file 
[cloudera@quickstart ~]$ cd Downloads/
[cloudera@quickstart Downloads]$ chmod 777 Anaconda3-2019.10-Linux-x86_64.sh 
[cloudera@quickstart Downloads]$ ./Anaconda3-2019.10-Linux-x86_64.sh 


Anaconda will be installed by default in the location below
[/home/cloudera/anaconda3] >>> 
PREFIX=/home/cloudera/anaconda3

3.  
Download spark from the below link: 
https://www.apache.org/dyn/closer.lua/spark/spark-2.4.4/spark-2.4.4-bin-hadoop2.6.tgz


4. Start Anaconda Navigator
Open Terminal 
cd /home/cloudera/anaconda3
./bin/anaconda-navigator

Click on launch buttonin Anaconda navigator

This will start your navigator and you can launch jupyter notebook by clicking on launch button in Anaconda Navigator. 

The following text file will open.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="1;url=http://localhost:8962/tree?token=27d4154cbaf8779cc5343dd1fdf1b1e07f38dacbd40e35c5" />
    <title>Opening Jupyter Notebook</title>
    <script>
      setTimeout(function() {
        window.location.href = "http://localhost:8962/tree?token=27d4154cbaf8779cc5343dd1fdf1b1e07f38dacbd40e35c5";
      }, 1000);
    </script>
</head>
<body>

<p>
    This page should redirect you to Jupyter Notebook. If it doesn't,
    <a href="http://localhost:8962/tree?token=27d4154cbaf8779cc5343dd1fdf1b1e07f38dacbd40e35c5">click here to go to Jupyter</a>.
</p>

</body>
</html>


Copy the url and p[aste it in the web browser. You will get Jupyter web interface. Open the code and execute

For Twitter Streaming:

install tweepy using the following command:

pip install tweepy

